    • writeHeader

      private void writeHeader(BufferedWriter writer, Class<?> clazz) throws IOException
      Private method for writing first lines of an implementation class. if given class is located in default package, it writes nothing, otherwise, it writes one line of code: package + name of package to which given class should belong followed by semicolon.
      Parameters:
      writer - Correct BufferedWriter to which implementation code should be written.
      clazz - class instance of interface for which methods should be implemented.
      Throws:
      IOException - If a writing error occurs.

    • writeClassDeclaration

      Private method for writing correct class declaration for the implementation of the given class token to the specified writer.
      Parameters:
      writer - BufferedWriter to which implementation class declaration should be written.
      token - Interface for which implementation is to be created.
      Throws:
      IOException - If a writing error occurs.

    • writeImplementations

      private void writeImplementations(BufferedWriter writer, Class<?> token) throws IOException
      Private method to generate implementation of the given interface to the specified writer. This method generates default code for all methods that require implementation, including methods from the interface which we are implementing and methods from interfaces the specified interface extends.
      Parameters:
      writer - BufferedWriter to which implementation of methods should be written.
      token - Interface for which implementation is to be created.
      Throws:
      IOException - If a writing error occurs.

    • writeMethod

      private void writeMethod(BufferedWriter writer, Method method) throws IOException
      Private method to write implementation of a single method. This is a helping method for writeImplementations(BufferedWriter, Class) method, this method correctly generates code for method's declaration, and default body of the given method.
      Parameters:
      writer - BufferedWriter to which the method's implementation should be written.
      method - Method instance to be implemented.
      Throws:
      IOException - If a writing error occurs.

    • produceArg

      private String produceArg(Class<?> clazz)
      Private method for generating code for a single argument for a method. This is a helping method for generateMethodArgs(Method) method, which is passed to typeWriter(Class[], Function) as predicate to generate code for all arguments of a method as T arg1, T arg2, T arg3,....
      Parameters:
      clazz - Type of parameter to be generated.
      Returns:
      A string with argument type, and default argument name.
      See Also:
      • writeType(Class)

    • generateMethodArgs

      private String generateMethodArgs(Method method)
      Private method for generating all arguments of the given method. This is a helping method for writeMethod(BufferedWriter, Method) to generate correct method's argument line of code.
      Parameters:
      method - Method for which code for arguments should be generated.
      Returns:
      A string with all arguments of the specified method.

    • generateMethodExceptions

      private String generateMethodExceptions(Method method)
      Private method for generating code for exceptions thrown by the specified method. This method generates a correct line of code that consists of throws and the corresponding exceptions thrown by the specified method, or an empty string if the method does not throw exceptions.
      Parameters:
      method - The method for which exceptions should be generated.
      Returns:
      A string with the sequence of exceptions thrown by the specified method, of an empty string if the method does not throw any exception.

    • typeWriter

      private String typeWriter(Class<?>[] classArr, Function<Class<?>,String> f)
      Private method for generating code for an array of classes. This is a helping method for generateMethodArgs(Method) and generateMethodExceptions(Method), it takes an array of classes for which code has to be generated, and predicate that specifies how to generate code string for these classes.
      Parameters:
      classArr - The array of classes for which code should be generated.
      f - A predicate that indicates how to generate code for classArr.
      Returns:
      A string with the code sequence for all classes given in classArr argument.

    • generateMethodBody

      private String generateMethodBody(Method method)
      Private method for generating default body for the specified method. This method generates code with a correct return statement for a with default primitive values if it returns a primitive type, null if returns a reference type, or an empty string if it is declared as void. This is a helping method for writeMethod(BufferedWriter, Method).
      Parameters:
      method - Method for which body has to be generated.
      Returns:
      A string with a correct return statement or an empty string for void methods.

      Parameters:
      clazz - Data type for which interpretable code should be generated.
      Returns:
      A string with interpretable java code.

    • getType

      private Class<?> getType(Class<?> clazz)
      Private method for getting the correct type name for a class. If it is an array class, it returns the type of elements of the array, otherwise it returns the given class parameter type.
      Parameters:
      clazz - class to get type from.
      Returns:
      The data type of the elements of an array or of the same class if it is not an array.

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: JarImpler
      Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Entry point for this class. To implement an interface and generate the corresponding jar file, three arguments have to be given.
      1. -jar
      2. Interface's canonical name for which implementation will be generated
      3. Output file name for generated jar file
      To generate only interface's implementation, only second and third argument have to be given (2 arguments in total), instead of jar file's path, root directory for implemented interface has to be specified as requested by implement(Class, Path).
      Parameters:
      args - list of parameters to be given to our program ( expected 2 or 3 arguments).
